Project Introduction¶

This dataset contains the booking information of City Hotel and Resort Hotel in 2022, including hotel bookings and cancellations, hotel bookings in each month, customer source and booking cancellation rate, customer type, hotel booking channel, average daily expenditure of various types of travelers, number of new and old customers and cancellation rate, deposit method and booking cancellation rate, room type and booking cancellation volume, etc.

  • Keywords

Data Exploration Analysis, Random Forest, XGBoost, Logistic Regression

3.10 Analysis Summary¶

    1. The booking volume and cancellation rate of City Hotel are much higher than those of Resort Hotel. The hotel should conduct customer surveys to gain a deeper understanding of the factors that lead customers to give up bookings, thereby reducing the customer cancellation rate.
    1. The hotel should make good use of the peak tourist season in July and August each year. It can increase prices appropriately to obtain more profits while ensuring service quality. It can also conduct preferential activities in the off-season (winter), such as Christmas promotions and New Year activities, to reduce hotel vacancy rates.
    1. The hotel needs to analyze the customer portraits from major source countries such as Portugal and the United Kingdom, understand the attribute labels, preferences and consumption characteristics of these customers, and launch exclusive services to reduce the customer cancellation rate.
    1. Since individual travelers are the main customer group of the hotel and have a high consumption level, the hotel can increase the publicity and marketing of free travel through online and offline travel agencies to attract more tourists of this type.
    1. The cancellation rate of new guests is 24% higher than that of old guests. Therefore, hotels should focus on the booking and check-in experience of new guests, provide more guidance and discounts for new guests, such as providing discounts for first-time guests, and survey new guests' feedback on satisfaction and dissatisfaction with their stay to improve future services, while maintaining good service for old guests.
    1. The cancellation rate of non-refundable deposits is as high as 99%. Hotels should optimize this method, such as returning 50% of the deposit, or directly canceling this method, so as to increase the occupancy rate.
    1. The cancellation rate of A and G room types is much higher than that of other room types. Hotels should carefully confirm room information with customers when booking, so that customers have a full understanding of the room situation and avoid cognitive errors. At the same time, they can optimize room facilities and improve service levels.

4 Data Preprocessing¶

The purpose of modeling is to predict whether a traveler will cancel a hotel reservation. Later, we need to set 'is_canceled' as the label y, and the rest as features x. The date features 'is_cance' and 'reservation_status_date' do not directly affect the label, so we delete them.

In [22]:
df1=df.drop(labels=['reservation_status_date'],axis=1)

5 Modeling and Prediction¶

In [42]:
# 划分特征x和标签y
x=df2.loc[:,df2.columns != 'is_canceled' ]
y=df2.loc[:,'is_canceled']
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split as tts
xtrain,xtest,ytrain,ytest=tts(x,y,test_size=0.3,random_state=90)
for i in [xtrain,xtest,ytrain,ytest]:
    i.index=range(i.shape[0])

5.1 Random Forest¶

In [43]:
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score as cvs,KFold
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
rfc=RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100,random_state=90)
cv=KFold(n_splits=10, shuffle = True, random_state=90)
rfc_score=cvs(rfc,xtrain,ytrain,cv=cv).mean()
rfc.fit(xtrain,ytrain)
y_score=rfc.predict_proba(xtest)[:,1]
rfc_pred=rfc.predict(xtest)
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve
from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score as AUC
FPR, recall, thresholds = roc_curve(ytest,y_score, pos_label=1)
rfc_auc = AUC(ytest,y_score)
In [44]:
plt.figure(figsize=(8,8))
plt.plot(FPR, recall, color='red',label='ROC curve (area = %0.2f)' % rfc_auc)
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='black', linestyle='--')
plt.xlim([-0.05, 1.05])
plt.ylim([-0.05, 1.05])
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('Recall')
plt.title('Random Forest Classifier ROC Curve')
plt.legend(loc="lower right")
plt.show()
